dc_title_s: A plan of the city of New-York; drawn by Major Holland, Surveyor General. 1776.
dc_description_s: Facsimile. Relief shown by hachures. Indexed. "Engr. for D.T. Valentine's Manual 1863 ..." From "Valentine's manual of the City of New York". 1 map; 33 x 39 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
